Shooters from Moulder Luggeweer Akademie (MLA) Club achieved various accolades and milestones at the Florida Skietklub (FSK) competition in Polokwane last Friday. Promising young and up-and-coming shooter, Migael Moulder broke his own u/12 record of 380 out of 400 which he set in February in Klerksdorp.  He managed to shoot 387 out of 400 during the competition, while Marzé Becker won a bronze medal in the u/20 precision and the 3P discipline in the u/16 division. Cara van der Merwe won bronze medals for the 3P and 10m standing position in the women’s category, while Shaun van den Heever claimed a silver medal in the 10m standing position for men. Their coach, Gene Moulder, received a gold medal in the 3P position and silver in the 10m standing position for seniors.